# PART 2: Push Maven Project to GitHub

---

## Step 7: Configure Git (only once)

```bash
git config --global user.name "yourname"
git config --global user.email "your@email.com"
```

Verify:

```bash
git config --list
```

---

## Step 8: Create repository in GitHub

Go to:

```
https://github.com
```

Steps:

* Click **New Repository**
* Name: `maven-project`
* Choose Public/Private
* DO NOT add README
* Click Create

(as shown in page 4) 

---

## Step 9: Go to your project

```bash
cd ~/migrate/Calculator
```

---

## Step 10: Initialize Git

```bash
git init
```

---

## Step 11: Create .gitignore

```bash
touch .gitignore
vim .gitignore
```

Paste:

```
target/
*.log
*.class
.idea/
.vscode/
```

Save:

```
ESC
:wq
```

---

## Step 12: Add and commit

```bash
git add .
git commit -m "Initial commit - Maven project"
```

---

## Step 13: Connect GitHub repo

```bash
git remote add origin https://github.com/username/maven-project.git
```

(Replace username)

---

## Step 14: Push code

```bash
git branch -M main
git push -u origin main
```

---

## Step 15: Enter credentials

Git will ask:

* Username → your GitHub username
* Password → **Personal Access Token (NOT password)**

---

## Step 16: Create Token

Go to:

```
GitHub → Profile → Settings → Developer settings
→ Personal access tokens → Generate new token
```

Select:

```
repo
```

Copy token → paste when asked

(as explained in page 5) 

---

# PART 3: Create Jenkins Pipeline

---

## Step 17: Create Pipeline Job

Go to Jenkins:

```
New Item → Pipeline
```

Give name:

```
Maven-Pipeline
```

Click OK

---

## Step 18: Add Pipeline Script

Scroll → Pipeline section

Paste:

```groovy
pipeline {
    agent any

    tools {
        maven 'Maven-3.9'
    }

    stages {

        stage('Checkout') {
            steps {
                git branch: 'main',
                url: 'https://github.com/username/maven-project.git'
            }
        }

        stage('Build') {
            steps {
                sh 'mvn clean package'
            }
        }

        stage('Test') {
            steps {
                sh 'mvn test'
            }
        }
    }
}
```

Replace:

```
username → your GitHub username
```

(as shown in page 6 highlighted part) 

Click **Save**

---

## Step 19: Run Pipeline

Click:

```
Build Now
```

(as shown in page 7 image) 

---

## Step 20: Check Output

Click build → Console Output

You should see:

```
BUILD SUCCESS
```

Pipeline stages:

* Checkout
* Build
* Test

All should be green

